<TITLE> International quality control conference on Oct 24 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 22 (bdnews24.com)  A three-day International Quality Control Circle Conference will start in Dhaka on October 24. AMM Khairul Bashar, secretary general of the Bangladesh Society for Total Quality Management known as BSTQM, told the media about the event at a press conference at the National Press Club on Monday. Bashar said nearly 1,000 representatives from some 14 countries were expected to attend the conference at the Dhaka Sheraton Hotel. He said some 500 representatives from Japan, South Korea, China, Taiwan, the Philippines, Singapore, Indonesia, Thailand and India had already registered for the event. Representatives from Malaysia, Hong Kong, Sri Lanka, Nepal and Pakistan would also attend the conference. He said the conference would discuss 155 case studies and 10 technical subjects. Development of steel, ship building, energy, textiles, electrical, chemicals, food, housing, defence, education and service sectors would be discussed in the three-day gathering, Bashar added. bdnews2
